  "texts": [
    "To address these challenges, PEFT was proposed 44.",
    "PEFT method involves fine-tuning only a small or additional set of model parameters while keeping the majority of pre-training parameters fixed, resulting in significant reductions in computation and storage costs.",
    "Moreover, advanced PEFT techniques such as Adapter-Tuning, Prefix-Tuning, P-Tuning, and LoRA have achieved performance comparable to full fine-tuning.",
    "Adapter-Tuning 45 involves inserting smaller neural network layers or modules (referred to as adapters) into each layer of the pre-trained model.",
    "During the fine-tuning process, the parameters of the original transformer are frozen, and only the parameters of the adapter layers are learned."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To address these challenges, PEFT was proposed 44."
  ]
}